> Hello @cbodonnell, is it possible to have a little example for limit bandwidth server side? I'm trying to write a plugin for this but without success.

@tecufanujacu I'll mention that you will need to set both the `bandwidth_limit` and `bandwidth_limit_mode` in the `content` field of the response to [`NewProxy`](https://github.com/fatedier/frp/blob/dev/doc/server_plugin.md#newproxy).

I don't have a full example, but these snippets show how you can do it:
```go
func handleNewProxy(w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request) {
  // ... parse metadata from the request

  // get the original `content` from the proxy metadata
  content, ok := metadata["content"].(map[string]interface{})
  if !ok {
    // ... handle no content
  }

  content["bandwidth_limit"] = "1250KB"
  content["bandwidth_limit_mode"] = "server"

  // ... any additional handler logic

  contentJSON, err := json.Marshal(content)
  if err != nil {
    // ... handle error
  }

  response := fmt.Sprintf("{\"reject\": false, \"content\": %s}", string(contentJSON))
  w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)
  w.Write([]byte(response))
}
```

