Could you also update this to use `sync.Once` to ensure it only closes once? This way, we can avoid using `PanicToError`.

A more comprehensive fix to this could remove the recursive call and swap function like so:

```go
type CloseNotifyConn struct {
    net.Conn
    closeOnce sync.Once
    closeFn func()
}

func (cc *CloseNotifyConn) Close() (err error) {
    cc.closeOnce.Do(func() {
        err = cc.Conn.Close()
        if cc.closeFn != nil {
            cc.closeFn()
        }
    })
    return
}
```

Same goes for the `StatsConn.Close()` in this file

```go
type StatsConn struct {
